name: Azat Zhakubayev
headline: SOC Analyst at Beeline üêù| IITU-CS
creator: True
bio:
As a SOC Analyst at Beeline Kazakhstan, a leading telecommunications company, I monitor and analyze information security events and incidents in the company's SIEM, install and configure agents for scaling SIEM, filter and correlate false positives, maintain a log of incidents, respond to and notify customers, and investigate and prepare recommendations for information security incidents. I have successfully handled multiple complex and critical incidents, ensuring timely resolution and customer satisfaction.

I am also a Bachelor's student in Cybersecurity at International Information Technologies University, where I have gained a solid foundation in network security, cryptography, malware analysis, and ethical hacking. I have also participated in a student exchange program at Innopolis University, a renowned institution for innovation and technology, where I have learned about artificial intelligence, cloud computing, and data science. Additionally, I have a previous experience as a System Administrator at Cushpen Innovations, where I integrated medical products with other systems and configured servers, including Windows administration. I am passionate about protecting data and systems from cyber threats, enhancing interoperability and efficiency of systems, and learning new technologies and skills. I am eager to apply my knowledge and skills to new challenges and opportunities, and to bring diverse perspectives and experiences to the team.

name: Sergey Alexandrov
headline: QA Automation Engineer | 3+ years in Fintech Test Automation (Python, PyTest, Appium, Selenium)
creator: False
school_2: Siberian State University of Geosystems and Technologies
bio:
Since my school years, I have been passionate about technical sciences and information technologies.
This interest led me to graduate from university with an engineering degree. During and after my studies, I was involved in the development and optimization of websites.

In 2020, I began learning the Python programming language and software testing. I completed several specialized courses and an internship at Tensor.
In 2021, I won a nationwide competition and received a grant from Ak Bars Bank to study at Innopolis University in the QA Automation Engineer Python program. After successfully graduating in 2022, I started my career at Ak Bars Digital.

Currently, I am a QA Automation Engineer with 3 years of experience in Python. I develop and maintain automated tests for APIs and UI using Selenium and Pytest in the fintech industry, integrating these tests into CI/CD processes.

Thanks to my expertise in framework development, I help teams optimize testing processes, reduce regression testing time, and ensure high-quality software delivery. I implemented automated testing frameworks that reduced release timelines by 3 days and ensured 100% uptime during live events through strict quality control and proactive issue resolution.

In 2023-2024, I completed the DevOps Champion course and an introductory database course at Ak Bars Digital. I also began learning English and previously studied German (B1 level).

Currently, I am starting the development of a testing automation framework for the Android mobile application "Resident Card of the Republic of Tatarstan" at Ak Bars Digital.

My experience includes the following technologies:
 - Programming languages: Python
 - Skills: Selenium, UI, API, Kubernetes, Docker, CI/CD
 - Repositories: GitHub, GitLab
 - Project trackers: Jira
 - Test Case Management: TestRail

I am always open to new professional challenges and connections. Let's talk: s.sdet@mail.ru

name: Gabriel Chung Thomas
headline: AI Researcher | Founder at GT Augment
creator: False
past_company_2: Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology (State University) - MIPT, Phystech
school_1: Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology (State University) (MIPT)
bio:
I am a founder, entrepreneur, and AI/ML engineer passionate about revolutionizing experiences through cutting-edge AI and AR technologies. 

Currently, I am the founder of GT Augment, an innovative AR platform that powers GT Merch (an interactive gifting startup I founded in 2022). At GT Augment, we are redefining augmented reality experiences, enabling users to create interactive, personalized products that transform everyday interactions into memorable and engaging moments. Our applications span various fields, including:

- Education: Crafting immersive learning environments with personalized, AI-driven content.
- Business: Enhancing product visualization through AR and driving decision-making with AI-driven insights.
- Marketing and Sales: Offering interactive product demonstrations that significantly boost customer engagement.
- Gifting: Creating customizable gifts that preserve memories and offer a novel way of gifting.

As an AI/ML Engineer, I am currently interning at Dugree in New York, USA, where I delve into the research and application of Large Language Models (LLMs) and Natural Language Processing (NLP). I collaborate with a team of experts to drive innovation in AI, contributing to Dugree's mission of fostering healthy and unbiased discourse.

My dual passion for technology and entrepreneurship equips me with a unique blend of technical expertise and business acumen. I thrive on tackling real-world challenges, leveraging my skills in AR, AI, machine learning, and data science to drive innovation and growth across various industries. I am committed to continuous learning and poised to lead the next generation of startups in setting new standards in the tech industry and beyond.

If you are an investor, startup enthusiast, or AI visionary interested in collaborating with me, please feel free to email me at gabrielchung50@gmail.com. Let's connect and explore the future of AI and AR together.

name: Khadija Fraz
location: Kingston Upon Hull, England, United Kingdom
headline: Tutor @ University of Hull | Machine Learning, Deep Learning | Systems and Data Partner @University of Hull
creator: False
bio:
As a Tutor and a Student Insight & Sector Policy Manager at University of Hull, I apply my data science skills and knowledge to two different domains: education and public sector. I mentor students in machine learning and deep learning, helping them master the concepts and tools that are essential for becoming proficient data scientists. I also analyze public sector data to generate actionable insights that can inform and enhance policy making and implementation.

I hold a Master's degree in Data Science and Artificial Intelligence from Innopolis University, where I participated in the Google Creative Campus program and published two papers in prestigious journals. My research interests include time series analysis, anomaly detection, and energy consumption. I am passionate about using data to solve real-world problems and create positive social impact. I seek to connect with other professionals and enthusiasts who share this vision and learn from their experiences and perspectives.

name: Sergei Aliseichik
headline: BIM Modeler | –°oordinator | Revit | ACC
creator: False

bio:
Netherlands based BIM coordinator and BIM modeler. 
I currently work as a modeler in the Water and Maritime industry. My main area of expertise is structural engineering.  However, in the past I have also worked on residential, industrial and infrastructure projects. This experience allows me to juggle knowledge and software products to use the best for complex projects at different stages. Examples of such multidisciplinary projects include a floating hotel, port development masterplans,  floating foundations for the world's most powerful wind turbines or NEOM.

BIM is not only my job but also my hobby. I really love it, so I follow the industry updates and try to implement new ways of working into the daily routine and improve the quality of the end result. For example, experimenting with Autodesk Forma for preliminary design. Parametric design models and generative design in Revit and Rhino Grasshopper


Advanced user of #Revit, #Navisworks, #BIM360 and #ACC Basic user of #Dynamo, Civil 3D, #Solibri. Knowledge of ISO 19650

name: Rishabh Upadhyay
location: Abu Dhabi Emirate, United Arab Emirates
headline: AI Agents | GenAI | Information Retrieval
creator: False
bio:
As an experienced Data Scientist specializing in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Machine Learning (ML), and Automatic Speech Recognition (ASR), I bring a robust portfolio of skills and accomplishments to the forefront of technological innovation in healthcare. Holding a Ph.D. in Information Retrieval from the University of Milano-Bicocca, my career has been marked by pivotal roles at institutions such as the Office of Health Economics in London and G42 (PAX-AI) in Abu Dhabi. 

My past projects includes the development of systems for analysing and retrieving truthful health documents, as well as designing tools to combat misinformation in digital spaces. These initiatives have leveraged my deep knowledge in NLP technologies such as Large Language Models to provide actionable, evidence-based insights. With numerous publications and participations in global conferences, I continue to contribute to academic and practical discussions surrounding the ethical and efficient application of AI in healthcare. I am also actively involved in community and academic endeavors, serving as a co-organizer and committee member for various workshops and conferences focused on information retrieval and health misinformation. 

Let's connect and explore how we can collaborate to harness the power of data and make a meaningful impact in the world.

name: Arthur Korochansky
headline: Senior Ruby Developer
creator: False
school_2: Southwest State University (former Kursk State Technical University)
bio:
Hi there! I can say about myself I'm so creative as so pragmatic person. In my projects I prefers flexible and elegant solutions, I'll never be waste time on something if it's have no any impact, but on other side I'm always focusing on code cleanliness and style, thoroughly designing code architecture. 

Every day I'm looking for tasks which can challenge with my professional and personal skills. In my job I like to have some creative space to reach my potential fully. Also, I like to work with open-mind people and I'm totally sure that the trust is a key to any positive result or success.

Basic, I'm Ruby evangelist, but I also tried different technologies in my previous life periods like Go, Java, Scala, C/C++, Python, Eiffel, JavaScript, RAD Studio, Android, so I'm always open to different offers. Actually, now I want to work with Crystal or Elixir.

You can say my main word in my life is "growth". Outside of my IT carrier, I learning sound design and making some beats. More I like to travel and meet interesting people who can teach me something new.

Check my coders rank: https://profile.codersrank.io/user/artk0de
